    },
    {
      "content": "You can use the Audience section to define a standard list of items to limit your campaign or limits your campaign based on customized criteria.",
      "pos": [
        6132,
        6276
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The standard set of options to Limit your Audience allows you to push to either new or old users or native push users only.",
      "pos": [
        6277,
        6400
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can also set a quota to limit the number of users who receive the push.",
      "pos": [
        6401,
        6476
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can manually Edit the expression for how your campaign is filtered to include one or more criterion to target users.",
      "pos": [
        6477,
        6597
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can manually type an audience expression.",
      "pos": [
        6598,
        6643
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Such an expression must explicitly define the relation between criteria.",
      "pos": [
        6644,
        6716
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A criterion is described by an identifier that must start with a capital letter and cannot contain spaces.",
      "pos": [
        6717,
        6823
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The relation between the criteria can be described using 'and', 'or', 'not' operators as well as '(', ')'.",
      "pos": [
        6824,
        6930
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Example: \"Criterion1 or (Criterion1 and not Criterion2)\".",
      "pos": [
        6931,
        6988
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note: With a large audience included in campaigns, the server side targeting scan can be slow, especially if you attempt to start multiple campaigns at the same time.",
      "pos": [
        6992,
        7158
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If possible, only start one campaign at a time.",
      "pos": [
        7162,
        7209
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "At the most, only start four campaigns at a time.",
      "pos": [
        7212,
        7261
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Push only to your active users (checkbox \"Engage only users who can be reached using Native Push\" and \"Engage only active users\") so that only your users who still have the app installed and use it will need to be scanned.",
      "pos": [
        7264,
        7486
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once your audience is defined, you can use the simulate button to find out how many users will receive this Push.",
      "pos": [
        7487,
        7600
